TITLE: Querying a record using Sails.js .findOne()
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates how to use the `.findOne()` method in Sails.js to find a user record in the database based on the username criteria. It uses `await` to handle the asynchronous operation and checks if a user was found before logging a message to the console. The Users model must be defined in your Sails.js application.
SOURCE: https://github.com/balderdashy/sails/blob/master/docs/reference/waterline/models/findOne.md#2025-04-20_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
var finn = await Users.findOne({
  username: 'finn'
});

if (!finn) {
  sails.log('Could not find Finn, sorry.');
}
else {
  sails.log('Found "%s"', finn.fullName);
}
```

