TITLE: Modern Actions2 Format Implementation
DESCRIPTION: Example of a modern actions2 format action that handles user welcome functionality with input validation and multiple exit conditions.
SOURCE: https://github.com/balderdashy/sails/blob/master/docs/concepts/ActionsAndControllers/ActionsAndControllers.md#2025-04-20_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
module.exports = {

  friendlyName: 'Welcome user',

  description: 'Look up the specified user and welcome them, or redirect to a signup page if no user was found.',

  inputs: {
    userId: {
      description: 'The ID of the user to look up.',
      type: 'number',
      required: true
    }
  },

  exits: {
    success: {
      responseType: 'view',
      viewTemplatePath: 'pages/welcome'
    },
    notFound: {
      description: 'No user with the specified ID was found in the database.',
      responseType: 'notFound'
    }
  },

  fn: async function ({userId}) {
    var user = await User.findOne({ id: userId });
    if (!user) { throw 'notFound'; }
    return {
      name: user.name
    };
  }
};
```

