TITLE: Accessing Raw Mongo Collection in Sails.js
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates how to access a raw Mongo collection instance from a Sails.js model using the `.manager` property. It requires the `sails-mongo` adapter and assumes a model named `Pet`. The `db` variable represents the Mongo client's `db` instance, allowing direct interaction with the database.
SOURCE: https://github.com/balderdashy/sails/blob/master/docs/reference/waterline/datastores/manager.md#2025-04-20_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
// Since the db connection manager exposed by `sails-mongo` is actually
// the same as the Mongo client's `db` instance, we can treat it as such.
var db = Pet.getDatastore().manager;

// Now we can do anything we could do with a Mongo `db` instance:
var rawMongoCollection = db.collection(Pet.tableName);
```

