TITLE: Configuring Session Handling with Asset Detection
DESCRIPTION: Example configuration in config/session.js demonstrating how to use the asset detection regex to selectively disable sessions for static asset requests while maintaining sessions for .json requests.
SOURCE: https://github.com/balderdashy/sails/blob/master/docs/reference/application/advanced-usage/sails.LOOKS_LIKE_ASSET_RX.md#2025-04-20_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
// In `config/session.js`
isSessionDisabled: function (req){

  if (req.path.match(/\.json$/)) {
    // Don't disable sessions.
    return;
  }

  var seemsToWantSomeOtherStaticAsset = !!req.path.match(sails.LOOKS_LIKE_ASSET_RX);
  if (seemsToWantSomeOtherStaticAsset) {
    // Disable sessions.
    return true;
  }

  // Otherwise, don't disable sessions.
  return;

}
```

